<caption id="1DC50ADA755D8128FF71C97EFB9DF874" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5066867" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5066867" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5066867/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" startId="13.[151,244,1871,1892]" targetBox="[192,1387,183,1854]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph id="49055A52755D8128FF71C97EFB9DF874" blockId="13.[151,1437,1871,2029]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755D8128FF71C97EFED3F8FD" bold="true" box="[151,261,1871,1892]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">FIGURE 2</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="8EBA21D1755D8128FEF6C97EFDE3F8FD" authorityName="Luteyn" authorityYear="2013" box="[272,565,1871,1892]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichanthum">
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755D8128FEF6C97EFDE3F8FD" box="[272,565,1871,1892]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Sphyrospermum dolichanthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755D8128FDA6C97EFD8EF8FD" bold="true" box="[576,600,1871,1892]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">A.</emphasis>
Habit showing pendent flowers and stems rooting at some nodes. 
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755D8128FB2BC97EFB32F8FD" bold="true" box="[1229,1252,1871,1892]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B.</emphasis>
Leaf undersurface. 
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755D8128FF71C941FF78F81C" bold="true" box="[151,174,1904,1925]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C.</emphasis>
Mature flower showing basal bracteoles, pedicel, calyx, and corolla. 
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755D8128FC85C941FCADF81C" bold="true" box="[867,891,1904,1925]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D.</emphasis>
Longitudinal section of corolla with some stamens. 
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755D8128FA63C941FA4AF81C" bold="true" box="[1413,1436,1904,1925]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E.</emphasis>
Longitudinal section of calyx showing ovules. 
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755D8128FD86C9A3FDA4F83E" bold="true" box="[608,626,1938,1959]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">F.</emphasis>
Four adjacent stamens in dorsal view, two adjacent stamens in ventral view, single stamen in dorsal view, and single stamen in lateral view; the outermost stamen is the only one drawn in its entirety, including the long tubules dehiscing apically by obliquely pores. Illustration by Bobbi Angell (drawn from holotype).
</paragraph>
</caption>
