<subSubSection id="01A009D9755E812BFF71CF2EFCFDFD25" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="49055A52755E812BFF71CF2EFECEFEF9" blockId="14.[151,1436,287,700]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755E812BFF71CF2EFDC7FEA0" bold="true" box="[151,529,287,313]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Distribution and phenology:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8EBA21D1755E812BFDF7CF11FC82FEA0" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1952" box="[529,852,288,313]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flaviflorum">
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755E812BFDF7CF11FC82FEA0" box="[529,852,288,313]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Sphyrospermum flaviflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="8B7E94B0755E812BFC19CF11FB91FEA3" box="[1023,1095,288,314]" country="Ecuador" name="Canar" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Cañar</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="31AD1AC2755E812BFBB5CF11FB63FEA3" box="[1107,1205,288,314]" name="Ecuador" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, where it flowers in September.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="49055A52755E812BFF20CF5CFD05FE37" blockId="14.[151,1436,287,700]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755E812BFF20CF5CFE3EFE1E" bold="true" box="[198,488,365,391]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Conservation status:—</emphasis>
It is only known from the 
<typeStatus id="9601E4F0755E812BFCC4CF5CFC85FE1E" box="[802,851,365,391]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
collection and the 
<typeStatus id="9601E4F0755E812BFBD1CF5CFBBEFE1E" box="[1079,1128,365,391]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
locality is now extremely degraded. Critically endangered [EN B1ab(i, iii)].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="49055A52755E812BFF20CF8BFCFDFD25" blockId="14.[151,1436,287,700]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755E812BFF20CF8BFE45FE4D" bold="true" box="[198,403,442,468]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Observations:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8EBA21D1755E812BFE75CF8BFD0BFE4A" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1952" box="[403,733,442,467]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flaviflorum">
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755E812BFE75CF8BFD0BFE4A" box="[403,733,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Sphyrospermum flaviflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by having a very short pedicel and small campanulate, yellow corollas that might become tinted with pink when exposed to the sun (fide Camp 
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755E812BFA62CFD0FF0CFDB8" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">in sched</emphasis>
.). 
<taxonomicName id="8EBA21D1755E812BFF1FCC39FD96FDB8" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1952" box="[249,576,520,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flaviflorum">
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755E812BFF1FCC39FD96FDB8" box="[249,576,520,545]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Sphyrospermum flaviflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to a small group that includes 
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755E812BFB0ECC39FE89FDD1" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="8EBA21D1755E812BFB0ECC39FA41FDB8" authorityName="Sleumer" authorityYear="1934" box="[1256,1431,520,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spruceanum">S. spruceanum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8EBA21D1755E812BFF71CC1EFE8CFDD1" box="[151,346,559,584]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolium">S. rotundifolium</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8EBA21D1755E812BFE7DCC1EFDB2FDD1" box="[411,612,559,584]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xanthocarpum">
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755E812BFE7DCC1EFDB2FDD1" box="[411,612,559,584]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. xanthocarpum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; species with which it has in common short pedicellate flowers with small, corollas (yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="8EBA21D1755E812BFE32CC64FD41FDF7" box="[468,663,597,622]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolium">
<emphasis id="7BCE8640755E812BFE32CC64FD41FDF7" box="[468,663,597,622]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. rotundifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
